Explain it like I'm 5 what is broken that 26,1 fixes that the current theory has issues withOkay, imagine your theory is like building a super-cool spaceship that‚Äôs supposed to explain everything in the universe (stars, atoms, gravity, dark energy, everything!).
Right now your spaceship has a weird engine with two clocks instead of one (that‚Äôs the two time dimensions in 24,2).
What‚Äôs broken with two clocks?

The spaceship keeps shaking really badly (ghosts and instability)
Two clocks make the rules of physics get confused. Things can go backward in time by accident, or imaginary fast particles (tachyons) appear and make everything fall apart. It‚Äôs like the engine is trying to run forward and backward at the same time ‚Äî very wobbly and dangerous.
Nobody believes the spaceship will really fly
Almost all scientists only use one clock (one time) in their designs. When you show them a spaceship with two clocks, they say ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs super strange and probably broken ‚Äî show me proof it won‚Äôt explode!‚Äù So they won‚Äôt help you fix it or fly it.

What does switching to 26,1 (one clock + lots of space directions) fix?
It‚Äôs like taking out the second clock and giving the spaceship a normal, calm engine that everyone already knows how to use.

No more crazy shaking
With only one clock, the rules stop fighting each other. No ghosts, no time-travel accidents, no exploding imaginary particles. The spaceship becomes much steadier and safer.
Scientists will actually look at it
Most big physics theories (especially string theory ones) already use one clock + extra space directions. When you show them your 26,1 spaceship, they go ‚ÄúOh, that‚Äôs a normal kind of engine ‚Äî I understand how that works. Let me see your ideas!‚Äù Instead of ‚ÄúTwo clocks?! Nope, too weird, I‚Äôm walking away.‚Äù
It‚Äôs easier to add the real-world stuff
Dark energy, particles, gravity ‚Äî all of those things are easier to connect when you‚Äôre using the same one-clock rule book that most physicists use. You don‚Äôt have to keep explaining ‚Äúbut my two clocks are special!‚Äù all the time.

In super simple words:
Your old theory = spaceship with two clocks ‚Üí shakes a lot, nobody trusts it, hard to fix problems.
New idea (26,1) = spaceship with one normal clock ‚Üí stops shaking, people are willing to look at it and help, easier to make it match the real universe.
It‚Äôs not quite as wild and exciting as two clocks, but it‚Äôs way more likely to actually fly one day. üòä

